VActually adverts are a pretty terrible way of giving people information about products, because it is biased. Word of mouth is better in every way, and the internet has made word of mouth extremely easy to access and propagate.\u000a\u000aIf anyone wants a particular product, nowadays they can look it up on the internet and find many competing options, and lots of information about those options. Trying to get the same thing from adverts will make you aware of fewer options.\u000a\u000aAdverts are not very good at giving people relevant information. Mostly they just try to associate a product with sex or stable family life. And even when they do try to inform, they cannot possibly give people all the information they want, because an advert cannot answer a question. Comprehensive product reviews on the internet are able to answer particular questions better.\u000a\u000aProbably the best way of getting information about products is through free samples, which are better than adverts.\u000a\u000a[[Free samples?|Free samples]]\u000a[[What about movie trailers? They give excellent information|Movie trailers]]\u000a
