VMovie trailers actually have more in common with "free samples" than adverts - although they can become adverts.\u000a\u000aA company making a film might put a trailer on youtube. That on its own does not involve paying anyone to recommend anything, so it is not advertizing.\u000a\u000aOne of your friends might post a link to the youtube trailer of the film on facebook - and still this is not an advert, nobody has been paid. It is just your friend being excited and recommending the film, and pointing people in the direction of a free sample.\u000a\u000aIf the film company pays a TV channel to broadcast the trailer, then THAT is an advert, because they probably wouldn't do it if they weren't being paid.\u000a\u000a[[So free samples are ok?|Free samples]]\u000a
